Key terms, concepts and schools of thought in project management; individual and organizational competencies and maturity models. Temporary and permanent processes and organisations, methods for their integration. Environments and life cycles of projects and programmes. Design and management of programmes, project portfolios and project organisations. Business plans, their main components and relations to projects (programmes).Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to teach basic knowledge on the management of projects, programmes, project portfolios and project organisations. Students acquire understanding of the essence of a business plan and relations to projects (programmes).Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course the student knows: - main terms and concepts of project management and their applications in various organizations and processes; - individual and organizational project management competence models; - theories explaining inter- and intra- organizational relations and typical structures project organizations; - main components of project and business plans and their relations and understands the essence of the role of project owner. After passing the course the student will be able to analyse business requirements and/or idea and to define projects (programmess) that fit into the project portfolio of the organisation.
